<content>== Description ==
This macro is wiki implementation of the LiveValidation's Validate.Presence functionality.
Reference: [[http://livevalidation.com/documentation#ValidatePresence]]

== Usage ==
Use this macro after calling ~{~{livevalidation /~}~} macro.
{{code}}
{{livevalidationPresence form='formId' property='propertyReference' failureMessage='Non empty value required.' /}}
{{/code}}
|= Param |= Description
| property | A property reference from document objects as described in [[http://extensions.xwiki.org/xwiki/bin/view/Extension/Model+Module#HPropertyReferences]]
| failureMessage | A string value to show on form a message in case of  validation failure.

== Examples ==
Add the following lines to MyApp.MyAppSheet.
{{code}}
{{livevalidation form='inline' object='MyApp.MyAppClass[0]' /}}
{{livevalidationPresence form='inline' property='MyApp.MyAppClass[0].myprop' failureMessage='myprop cannot be empty.' /}}
{{/code}}

